flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement|application_3|3|Invite a different option|When the discussed answer feels too fixed, bring in Creative Movement. Try a different frame, route, or explanation before you treat the response as final.|creative_movement|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_physical_rhythm_creative_movement::application_3
flow_state|social_exchange_creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm|application_1|1|Use response to get started|Start by saying the idea aloud, asking a question, or using a quick conversation to expose what the work needs. Keep the exchange focused on the next decision.|social_exchange|active|flow_state::social_exchange_creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm::application_1
flow_state|social_exchange_creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm|application_2|2|Shape options while they are live|Bring in Creative Movement during the exchange. Try another example, route, or wording, then use Deep Focus to develop the option that still makes sense afterwards.|creative_movement|active|flow_state::social_exchange_creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm::application_2
flow_state|social_exchange_creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm|application_3|3|Use rhythm to clear the process|When conversation and ideas start to run hot, bring in Physical Rhythm. Step away, move, or change setting before you return to the strongest option.|physical_rhythm|active|flow_state::social_exchange_creative_movement_deep_focus_physical_rhythm::application_3
flow_state|social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_deep_focus|application_1|1|Start with a live sense-check|Start by sharing the rough idea or question early enough for it to change. Ask what is clear, what is missing, and what the next step should serve.|social_exchange|active|flow_state::social_exchange_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_deep_focus::application_1
